{
  "message": "fuzz(alloc-bitmap): 25 structured seeds across bitmap operation surface\n\nExisting 17 seeds left several boundary classes uncovered. Add 25\nseeds spanning the bitmap's get/set/clear/find_free/find_contiguous\noperation matrix:\n\n  bitmap shapes:\n    * empty (0 bytes)\n    * 1-byte: all-zero, all-one, 0xAA / 0x55 alternating\n    * 8 / 16 / 128 (max) byte sizes\n    * leading 4 ones + trailing 4 zeros (find_free returns 32)\n    * sparse one-bit-at-100 (16 bytes)\n    * one bit per byte (worst case for find_contiguous)\n    * two zero runs separated by ones\n    * only bit 0 free (rest set)\n\n  index / count / start / len boundaries:\n    * idx = bit_count exactly\n    * idx > bit_count (model_get returns true for OOB)\n    * idx = u32::MAX-1 (huge value)\n    * count = 0\n    * len = 0 (find_contiguous returns Some(0))\n    * len > count (must return None)\n    * len exactly = count (whole-bitmap fit)\n    * len near upper boundary (count + 7)\n    * start > count (wrap-search second pass)\n\n1.6M runs / 11s post-seed surface no crashes.",
